            <thetext>``qx.lang.normalize.Date`` is missing ``Date.prototype.toISOString`` (and ``toJSON`` synonym). 

It&#39;s more complicated with ``Date.parse``. IE8 has ``Date.parse`` but it fails on most important application, an ISO8601 string, of JSON date interchange. So it should probably be replaced with ISO-compatible implementation. 

Both can be borrowed from es5-shim (https://github.com/kriskowal/es5-shim). Or implemented with ``qx.lang.Json`` and ``new qx.util.format.DateFormat(&#39;isoUtcDateTime&#39;).parse``. The latter however fails on date strings with milliseconds (e.g. 2011-10-09T07:06:05.123Z).</thetext>
